{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870262504,"sessionID":"ses_285e27dfcffeJkaP47XzFuVBZN","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1db2600013KlmgRJoUS7sMR","messageID":"msg_d7a1da16b001r3PbMNyDaev12A","sessionID":"ses_285e27dfcffeJkaP47XzFuVBZN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-22d6dc60a547475185299fc8b38a99a2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: Build command for AgentCube CLI that constructs container images from packaged agent workspaces. Orchestrates the full build lifecycle: prerequisite validation, version increment, Docker SDK build execution, and metadata persistence.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                        User Environment                          │\n24: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n25: │                                                                  │\n26: │   ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐    │\n27: │   │ Agent        │     │ agent_       │     │ Dockerfile   │    │\n28: │   │ Workspace    │────▶│ metadata.    │────▶│ (generated   │    │\n29: │   │ (./my-agent) │     │ yaml         │     │ by pack)     │    │\n30: │   └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘    │\n31: │          │                   │                    │              │\n32: │          └───────────────────┴────────────────────┘              │\n33: │                              │                                   │\n34: │                              ▼                                   │\n35: │                    ┌──────────────────┐                          │\n36: │                    │ kubectl-agentcube│                          │\n37: │                    │     build -f .   │                          │\n38: │                    └──────────────────┘                          │\n39: │                              │                                   │\n40: └──────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────┘\n41:                                │\n42:                                ▼\n43: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                     AgentCube CLI                                │\n45: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n46: │                                                                  │\n47: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n48: │   │                  CLI Layer (main.py)                     │   │\n49: │   │  ┌─────────┐                                             │   │\n50: │   │  │ build() │  Typer command handler                      │   │\n51: │   │  │         │  - Parse options                            │   │\n52: │   │  │         │  - Rich Progress spinner                    │   │\n53: │   │  │         │  - Error handling via _handle_error         │   │\n54: │   │  └─────────┘                                             │   │\n55: │   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n56: │                           │                                      │\n57: │                           ▼                                      │\n58: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n59: │   │                Runtime Layer                             │   │\n60: │   │  ┌──────────────┐                                        │   │\n61: │   │  │ BuildRuntime │  Orchestration class                   │   │\n62: │   │  │              │  - build() main entry                  │   │\n63: │   │  │              │  - _increment_version()                │   │\n64: │   │  │              │  - _validate_build_prerequisites()    │   │\n65: │   │  │              │  - _build_local() / _build_cloud()    │   │\n66: │   │  │              │  - _update_build_metadata()           │   │\n67: │   │  └──────────────┘                                        │   │\n68: │   └───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n69: │                           │                                      │\n70: │                           ▼                                      │\n71: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n72: │   │                Service Layer                             │   │\n73: │   │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                     │   │\n74: │   │  │ DockerService│  │MetadataService│                    │   │\n75: │   │  │              │  │               │                     │   │\n76: │   │  │ - check_     │  │ - load_       │                     │   │\n77: │   │  │   docker_    │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n78: │   │  │   available()│  │ - save_       │                     │   │\n79: │   │  │ - build_     │  │   metadata()  │                     │   │\n80: │   │  │   image()    │  │               │                     │   │\n81: │   │  │ - get_       │  │               │                     │   │\n82: │   │  │   image_     │  │               │                     │   │\n83: │   │  │   info()     │  │               │                     │   │\n84: │   │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                     │   │\n85: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n86: │                                                                  │\n87: └───────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────────┘\n88:                                 │\n89:                                 ▼\n90: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n91: │                     External Systems                             │\n92: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n93: │                                                                  │\n94: │   ┌──────────────┐          ┌──────────────┐                    │\n95: │   │ Docker       │          │ Metadata     │                    │\n96: │   │ Daemon       │◀────────▶│ YAML File    │                    │\n97: │   │ (dockerd)    │          │ (workspace)  │                    │\n98: │   └──────────────┘          └──────────────┘                    │\n99: │                                                                  │\n100: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n101: ```\n102: \n103: ### Component Diagram\n104: \n105: ```\n106: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n107: │                         agentcube/runtime/                          │\n108: ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n109: │                                                                     │\n110: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n111: │  │                    BuildRuntime                               │  │\n112: │  ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤  │\n113: │  │ Fields:                                                       │  │\n114: │  │   - verbose: bool                                             │  │\n115: │  │   - docker_service: DockerService                             │  │\n116: │  │   - metadata_service: MetadataService                         │  │\n117: │  │                                                               │  │\n118: │  │ Methods:                                                      │  │\n119: │  │   + build(workspace_path: Path, **options) → Dict[str, Any]   │  │\n120: │  │   + _increment_version(workspace_path, metadata) → str       │  │\n121: │  │   + _validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path) → None     │  │\n122: │  │   + _build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n123: │  │   + _build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options) → Dict   │  │\n124: │  │   + _update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata,         │  │\n125: │  │                           build_result, tag) → None           │  │\n126: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n127: │                                                                     │\n128: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n129: \n130: ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n131: │                         agentcube/services/                        │\n132: ├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n133: │                                                                     │\n134: │  ┌────────────────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐    │\n135: │  │       DockerService        │  │      MetadataService       │    │\n136: │  ├────────────────────────────┤  ├────────────────────────────┤    │\n137: │  │ Fields:                    │  │ Fields:                    │    │\n138: │  │   - verbose: bool          │  │   - verbose: bool          │    │\n139: │  │   - client: DockerClient   │  │                            │    │\n140: │  │                            │  │ Methods:                   │    │\n141: │  │ Methods:                   │  │   + load_metadata()        │    │\n142: │  │   + check_docker_available│  │   + save_metadata()        │    │\n143: │  │   + build_image()          │  │   + update_metadata()      │    │\n144: │  │   + get_image_info()       │  │                            │    │\n145: │  │   + push_image()           │  │                            │    │\n146: │  │   + remove_image()         │  │                            │    │\n147: │  └────────────────────────────┘  └────────────────────────────┘    │\n148: │                                                                     │\n149: └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ### Request Flow\n153: \n154: ```\n155: User Input: kubectl-agentcube build -f ./my-agent --verbose\n156: \n157:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n158:                 │  CLI Entry (main.py)                    │\n159:                 │                                         │\n160:                 │  1. Parse Typer options                 │\n161:                 │     - workspace: str                    │\n162:                 │     - proxy: Optional[str]              │\n163:                 │     - cloud_provider: Optional[str]     │\n164:                 │     - output: Optional[str]             │\n165:                 │     - verbose: bool                     │\n166:                 │                                         │\n167:                 │  2. Initialize BuildRuntime(verbose)    │\n168:                 │                                         │\n169:                 │  3. Start Rich Progress spinner         │\n170:                 │                                         │\n171:                 │  4. Call runtime.build(workspace, ...)  │\n172:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n173:                                  │\n174:                                  ▼\n175:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n176:                 │  BuildRuntime.build()                   │\n177:                 │                                         │\n178:                 │  Step 1: Load metadata                  │\n179:                 │     metadata_service.load_metadata()    │\n180:                 │     → AgentMetadata                     │\n181:                 │                                         │\n182:                 │  Step 2: Validate prerequisites         │\n183:                 │     _validate_build_prerequisites()     │\n184:                 │     - Check Docker available            │\n185:                 │     - Check Dockerfile exists           │\n186:                 │                                         │\n187:                 │  Step 3: Increment version              │\n188:                 │     original_version = metadata.version │\n189:                 │     new_tag = _increment_version()      │\n190:                 │     - X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1)                 │\n191:                 │     - v1.0 → v1.0.1                     │\n192:                 │     - None → \"latest\"                   │\n193:                 │                                         │\n194:                 │  Step 4: Execute build                  │\n195:                 │     if build_mode == \"local\":           │\n196:                 │         result = _build_local()         │\n197:                 │     else:                               │\n198:                 │         result = _build_cloud()         │\n199:                 │                                         │\n200:                 │  Step 5: Handle result                  │\n201:                 │     if success:                         │\n202:                 │         _update_build_metadata()        │\n203:                 │         return result                   │\n204:                 │     if failure:                         │\n205:                 │         rollback version to original    │\n206:                 │         raise RuntimeError              │\n207:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n208:                                  │\n209:                                  ▼\n210:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n211:                 │  BuildRuntime._build_local()            │\n212:                 │                                         │\n213:                 │  1. Resolve image name                  │\n214:                 │     image_name = f\"{agent_name}:{tag}\"  │\n215:                 │                                         │\n216:                 │  2. Build with Docker SDK               │\n217:                 │     docker_service.build_image(         │\n218:                 │         dockerfile_path=workspace/      │\n219:                 │                       Dockerfile,       │\n220:                 │         context_path=workspace,         │\n221:                 │         image_name=image_name,          │\n222:                 │         tag=tag,                        │\n223:                 │         build_args={                    │\n224:                 │             \"PROXY\": proxy              │\n225:                 │         } if proxy else None            │\n226:                 │     )                                   │\n227:                 │                                         │\n228:                 │  3. Get image info                      │\n229:                 │     docker_service.get_image_info()     │\n230:                 │     → image_id, image_size              │\n231:                 │                                         │\n232:                 │  4. Return build result dict            │\n233:                 │     {                                   │\n234:                 │         \"image_name\": \"...\",            │\n235:                 │         \"image_id\": \"...\",              │\n236:                 │         \"image_size\": \"...\",            │\n237:                 │         \"build_time\": \"...\",            │\n238:                 │         \"tag\": tag                      │\n239:                 │     }                                   │\n240:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n241:                                  │\n242:                                  ▼\n243:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n244:                 │  DockerService.build_image()            │\n245:                 │                                         │\n246:                 │  1. Get Docker client                   │\n247:                 │     client = docker.from_env()          │\n248:                 │                                         │\n249:                 │  2. Build image with streaming          │\n250:                 │     for line in client.api.build(       │\n251:                 │         path=str(context_path),         │\n252:                 │         dockerfile=str(dockerfile),     │\n253:                 │         tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",      │\n254:                 │         buildargs=build_args,           │\n255:                 │         decode=True                     │\n256:                 │     ):                                  │\n257:                 │         if verbose: log each line      │\n258:                 │                                         │\n259:                 │  3. Measure build time                  │\n260:                 │     start_time → end_time               │\n261:                 │                                         │\n262:                 │  4. Return structured result            │\n263:                 └────────────────┬────────────────────────┘\n264:                                  │\n265:                                  ▼\n266:                 ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n267:                 │  CLI Output                             │\n268:                 │                                         │\n269:                 │  Success:                               │\n270:                 │    [green] Build completed successfully │\n271:                 │    Image: {image_name}:{tag}            │\n272:                 │    Image ID: {image_id}                 │\n273:                 │    Size: {image_size}                   │\n274:                 │    Build time: {build_time}s            │\n275:                 │                                         │\n276:                 │  Failure:                               │\n277:                 │    [red] Error build: {error}           │\n278:                 │    [if verbose] Full traceback          │\n279:                 │    Exit code: 1                         │\n280:                 └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n281: ```\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## Data Structures\n286: \n287: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n288: \n289: Build command modifies and reads these fields:\n290: \n291: ```python\n292: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n293:     agent_name: str                      # Used for image name\n294:     description: Optional[str] = None\n295:     language: str = \"python\"\n296:     entrypoint: str                      # Dockerfile ENTRYPOINT\n297:     port: int = 8080                     # Dockerfile EXPOSE\n298:     build_mode: str = \"local\"            # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n299:     region: Optional[str] = None\n300:     version: Optional[str] = None        # Incremented on build\n301:     image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None  # Updated with build result\n302:     auth: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n303:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = \"requirements.txt\"\n304:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n305:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n306:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n307:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = None\n308:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None\n309:     router_url: Optional[str] = None\n310:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None\n311:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None\n312:     agent_id: Optional[str] = None\n313:     session_id: Optional[str] = None\n314:     k8s_deployment: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None\n315: \n316:     @field_validator(\"language\")\n317:     @classmethod\n318:     def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n319:         allowed = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n320:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n321:             raise ValueError(f\"language must be one of {allowed}\")\n322:         return v.lower()\n323: \n324:     @field_validator(\"build_mode\")\n325:     @classmethod\n326:     def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n327:         allowed = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n328:         if v.lower() not in allowed:\n329:             raise ValueError(f\"build_mode must be one of {allowed}\")\n330:         return v.lower()\n331: \n332:     @field_validator(\"port\")\n333:     @classmethod\n334:     def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n335:         if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n336:             raise ValueError(\"port must be between 1 and 65535\")\n337:         return v\n338: ```\n339: \n340: ### image Field Structure\n341: \n342: ```python\n343: image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = {\n344:     \"image_name\": str,       # e.g., \"my-agent\"\n345:     \"image_id\": str,         # Docker image ID (sha256:...)\n346:     \"image_size\": str,       # Human-readable size (e.g., \"125.3 MB\")\n347:     \"build_time\": float,     # Build duration in seconds\n348:     \"tag\": str,              # Image tag (e.g., \"v1.0.1\" or \"latest\")\n349: }\n350: ```\n351: \n352: ### BuildResult (Internal)\n353: \n354: ```python\n355: BuildResult = Dict[str, Any] = {\n356:     \"image_name\": str,\n357:     \"image_id\": str,\n358:     \"image_size\": str,\n359:     \"build_time\": float,\n360:     \"tag\": str,\n361:     \"success\": bool,\n362:     \"error\": Optional[str],\n363: }\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## API Contracts\n369: \n370: ### Command Interface\n371: \n372: | Command | Arguments | Description |\n373: |---------|-----------|-------------|\n374: | `build` | `--workspace` `-f` | Path to agent workspace directory (default: `.`) |\n375: | `build` | `--proxy` `-p` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n376: | `build` | `--cloud-provider` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n377: | `build` | `--output` | Output path for build artifacts |\n378: | `build` | `--verbose` | Enable detailed logging |\n379: \n380: ### Typer Command Signature\n381: \n382: ```python\n383: @app.command()\n384: def build(\n385:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\n386:         \".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\",\n387:         help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n388:         show_default=True\n389:     ),\n390:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n391:         None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\",\n392:         help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution\"\n393:     ),\n394:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n395:         None, \"--cloud-provider\",\n396:         help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"\n397:     ),\n398:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(\n399:         None, \"--output\",\n400:         help=\"Output path for build artifacts\"\n401:     ),\n402:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n403:         False, \"--verbose\",\n404:         help=\"Enable detailed logging\"\n405:     ),\n406: ) -> None:\n407:     \"\"\"Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n408:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n409:     \n410:     with Progress(\n411:         SpinnerColumn(),\n412:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n413:         console=console,\n414:     ) as progress:\n415:         task = progress.add_task(\"Building agent image...\", total=None)\n416:         \n417:         try:\n418:             runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n419:             result = runtime.build(\n420:                 workspace_path,\n421:                 proxy=proxy,\n422:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n423:                 output=output,\n424:             )\n425:             progress.update(task, description=\"Build completed\")\n426:             \n427:             console.print(f\"[green]Build completed successfully[/green]\")\n428:             console.print(f\"Image: {result['image_name']}:{result['tag']}\")\n429:             console.print(f\"Image ID: {result['image_id']}\")\n430:             console.print(f\"Size: {result['image_size']}\")\n431:             console.print(f\"Build time: {result['build_time']}s\")\n432:             \n433:         except Exception as e:\n434:             progress.stop()\n435:             _handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)\n436: ```\n437: \n438: ### BuildRuntime.build() Contract\n439: \n440: ```python\n441: def build(\n442:     self,\n443:     workspace_path: Path,\n444:     **options: Any,\n445: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n446:     \"\"\"\n447:     Build container image from workspace.\n448:     \n449:     Args:\n450:         workspace_path: Path to agent workspace directory\n451:         options: Build options including:\n452:             - proxy: Optional[str] - Proxy URL for build args\n453:             - cloud_provider: Optional[str] - Cloud provider name\n454:             - output: Optional[str] - Output path\n455:     \n456:     Returns:\n457:         Dict containing:\n458:             - image_name: str\n459:             - image_id: str\n460:             - image_size: str\n461:             - build_time: float\n462:             - tag: str\n463:     \n464:     Raises:\n465:         RuntimeError: If Docker is not available\n466:         ValueError: If Dockerfile does not exist\n467:         RuntimeError: If build fails (version rolled back)\n468:     \"\"\"\n469: ```\n470: \n471: ### DockerService.build_image() Contract\n472: \n473: ```python\n474: def build_image(\n475:     self,\n476:     dockerfile_path: Path,\n477:     context_path: Path,\n478:     image_name: str,\n479:     tag: str = \"latest\",\n480:     build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n481: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n482:     \"\"\"\n483:     Build Docker image using Docker SDK.\n484:     \n485:     Args:\n486:         dockerfile_path: Path to Dockerfile\n487:         context_path: Build context directory\n488:         image_name: Image name without tag\n489:         tag: Image tag\n490:         build_args: Optional build arguments (e.g., {\"PROXY\": url})\n491:     \n492:     Returns:\n493:         Dict containing:\n494:             - image_name: str (name:tag)\n495:             - image_id: str (sha256 digest)\n496:             - image_size: str (human-readable)\n497:             - build_time: float (seconds)\n498:     \n499:     Raises:\n500:         docker.errors.BuildError: If build fails\n501:         docker.errors.APIError: If Docker API error\n502:     \"\"\"\n503: ```\n504: \n505: ---\n506: \n507: ## Error Handling\n508: \n509: ### Error Categories\n510: \n511: | Category | Condition | Action |\n512: |----------|-----------|--------|\n513: | Docker Unavailable | `docker.from_env()` fails | Raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` |\n514: | Missing Dockerfile | No `Dockerfile` in workspace | Raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")` |\n515: | Build Failure | Docker build returns error | Rollback version, raise `RuntimeError` |\n516: | Invalid Metadata | Pydantic validation fails | Propagate `ValidationError` |\n517: | Version Rollback | Build fails after increment | Restore original version in metadata file |\n518: \n519: ### _handle_error() Pattern\n520: \n521: ```python\n522: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n523:     \"\"\"\n524:     Unified error handler for CLI commands.\n525:     \n526:     Prints error message in red, optionally shows traceback,\n527:     and exits with code 1.\n528:     \"\"\"\n529:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n530:     if verbose:\n531:         console.print_exception()\n532:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Version Rollback Logic\n536: \n537: ```python\n538: def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n539:     \"\"\"\n540:     Increment version with rollback capability.\n541:     \n542:     Returns new tag; caller must rollback on failure.\n543:     \"\"\"\n544:     original_version = metadata.version\n545:     try:\n546:         # Increment logic\n547:         if metadata.version:\n548:             if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(metadata.version):\n549:                 v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(metadata.version)\n550:                 new_version = str(v.bump_patch())\n551:             elif metadata.version.startswith(\"v\"):\n552:                 # v1.0 → v1.0.1\n553:                 base = metadata.version[1:]\n554:                 new_version = f\"v{base}.1\"\n555:             else:\n556:                 # Fallback: append -1\n557:                 new_version = f\"{metadata.version}-1\"\n558:         else:\n559:             new_version = \"latest\"\n560:         \n561:         metadata.version = new_version\n562:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n563:         return new_version\n564:         \n565:     except Exception:\n566:         metadata.version = original_version\n567:         raise\n568: ```\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## Testing Strategy\n573: \n574: ### Unit Tests\n575: \n576: | Test File | Coverage |\n577: |-----------|----------|\n578: | `tests/test_build_runtime.py` | BuildRuntime methods |\n579: | `tests/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService methods |\n580: | `tests/test_version_increment.py` | Version bump edge cases |\n581: \n582: ### Test Cases\n583: \n584: #### BuildRuntime Tests\n585: \n586: ```python\n587: class TestBuildRuntime:\n588:     def test_build_local_success(self, mock_docker_service, mock_metadata):\n589:         \"\"\"Successful local build returns image info.\"\"\"\n590:         \n591:     def test_build_docker_unavailable(self, mock_docker_unavailable):\n592:         \"\"\"Raises RuntimeError when Docker not running.\"\"\"\n593:         \n594:     def test_build_missing_dockerfile(self, workspace_no_dockerfile):\n595:         \"\"\"Raises ValueError when Dockerfile missing.\"\"\"\n596:         \n597:     def test_version_increment_semver(self):\n598:         \"\"\"X.Y.Z → X.Y.(Z+1) for valid semver.\"\"\"\n599:         \n600:     def test_version_increment_v_prefix(self):\n601:         \"\"\"v1.0 → v1.0.1 for v-prefixed versions.\"\"\"\n602:         \n603:     def test_version_increment_fallback(self):\n604:         \"\"\"custom → custom-1 for non-semver strings.\"\"\"\n605:         \n606:     def test_version_rollback_on_failure(self, mock_build_failure):\n607:         \"\"\"Original version restored when build fails.\"\"\"\n608:         \n609:     def test_build_cloud_placeholder(self):\n610:         \"\"\"Cloud build returns placeholder dict.\"\"\"\n611: ```\n612: \n613: #### DockerService Tests\n614: \n615: ```python\n616: class TestDockerService:\n617:     def test_check_docker_available_running(self, mock_docker_client):\n618:         \"\"\"Returns True when Docker daemon running.\"\"\"\n619:         \n620:     def test_check_docker_available_not_running(self):\n621:         \"\"\"Returns False when Docker daemon unavailable.\"\"\"\n622:         \n623:     def test_build_image_success(self, mock_docker_api):\n624:         \"\"\"build_image returns image info dict.\"\"\"\n625:         \n626:     def test_build_image_with_proxy(self, mock_docker_api):\n627:         \"\"\"Proxy passed as build_arg.\"\"\"\n628:         \n629:     def test_get_image_info(self, mock_image):\n630:         \"\"\"Extracts image_id and size.\"\"\"\n631:         \n632:     def test_push_image_with_auth(self, mock_registry):\n633:         \"\"\"Login and push with credentials.\"\"\"\n634:         \n635:     def test_remove_image_success(self, mock_image):\n636:         \"\"\"Returns True on removal.\"\"\"\n637:         \n638:     def test_remove_image_failure(self):\n639:         \"\"\"Returns False, logs warning.\"\"\"\n640: ```\n641: \n642: ### Integration Tests\n643: \n644: ```python\n645: class TestBuildIntegration:\n646:     def test_full_build_workflow(self, packaged_workspace):\n647:         \"\"\"End-to-end: validate → increment → build → update metadata.\"\"\"\n648:         \n649:     def test_build_after_pack(self, agent_workspace):\n650:         \"\"\"Pack creates Dockerfile, build succeeds.\"\"\"\n651:         \n652:     def test_rebuild_increments_version(self, built_workspace):\n653:         \"\"\"Second build bumps version again.\"\"\"\n654: ```\n655: \n656: ### Test Fixtures\n657: \n658: ```python\n659: @pytest.fixture\n660: def mock_docker_service():\n661:     \"\"\"Mock DockerService with fake client.\"\"\"\n662:     \n663: @pytest.fixture\n664: def packaged_workspace(tmp_path):\n665:     \"\"\"Temporary workspace with Dockerfile and metadata.\"\"\"\n666:     \n667: @pytest.fixture\n668: def mock_build_failure():\n669:     \"\"\"Mock Docker SDK to raise BuildError.\"\"\"\n670: ```\n671: \n672: ---\n673: \n674: ## File Structure\n675: \n676: ```\n677: cmd/cli/\n678: ├── pyproject.toml\n679: ├── agentcube/\n680: │   ├── __init__.py\n681: │   ├── cli/\n682: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n683: │   │   └── main.py              # build command addition\n684: │   ├── models/\n685: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n686: │   │   └── pack_models.py       # MetadataOptions (shared)\n687: │   ├── runtime/\n688: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n689: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n690: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py     # NEW: BuildRuntime\n691: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py   # Future\n692: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py    # Future\n693: │   │   └── status_runtime.py    # Future\n694: │   ├── services/\n695: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n696: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py  # Existing\n697: │   │   ├── docker_service.py    # NEW: DockerService\n698: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py      # Future\n699: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py # Future\n700: │   └── operations/\n701: │       └── __init__.py\n702: ├── examples/\n703: │   ├── hello-agent/\n704: │   │   └── main.py\n705: │   └── math-agent/\n706: │       └── main.py\n707: └── tests/\n708:     ├── __init__.py\n709:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py      # Existing\n710:     ├── test_build_runtime.py     # NEW\n711:     ├── test_docker_service.py    # NEW\n712:     └── test_version_increment.py # NEW\n713: ```\n714: \n715: ---\n716: \n717: ## Dependencies\n718: \n719: ### Runtime Dependencies\n720: \n721: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n722: |---------|---------|---------|\n723: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; local build execution |\n724: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n725: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file I/O |\n726: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, console output |\n727: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic version parsing and bumping |\n728: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n729: \n730: ### Dev Dependencies\n731: \n732: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n733: |---------|---------|---------|\n734: | `pytest` | `>=7.4.0` | Test framework |\n735: | `pytest-asyncio` | `>=0.21.0` | Async test support |\n736: | `pytest-cov` | `>=4.1.0` | Coverage reporting |\n737: | `pytest-mock` | `>=3.11.0` | Mocking fixtures |\n738: | `ruff` | `>=0.1.0` | Linting |\n739: | `mypy` | `>=1.5.0` | Type checking |\n740: \n741: ### Optional Dependencies\n742: \n743: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n744: |---------|---------|---------|\n745: | `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client (for publish command) |\n746: \n747: ---\n748: \n749: ## Implementation Notes\n750: \n751: ### Version Increment Strategy\n752: \n753: ```python\n754: def _increment_version(workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str:\n755:     \"\"\"\n756:     Semver bump strategy:\n757:     \n758:     1. Valid semver (X.Y.Z): bump_patch → X.Y.(Z+1)\n759:        Example: 1.2.3 → 1.2.4\n760:     \n761:     2. v-prefixed non-semver (vX.Y): append .1\n762:        Example: v1.0 → v1.0.1\n763:     \n764:     3. Non-semver string: append -1\n765:        Example: custom → custom-1\n766:     \n767:     4. None/empty: use \"latest\"\n768:     \"\"\"\n769:     import semver\n770:     \n771:     if not metadata.version:\n772:         return \"latest\"\n773:     \n774:     version_str = metadata.version\n775:     \n776:     if semver.VersionInfo.isvalid(version_str.lstrip(\"v\")):\n777:         base = version_str.lstrip(\"v\")\n778:         v = semver.VersionInfo.parse(base)\n779:         new_v = v.bump_patch()\n780:         prefix = \"v\" if version_str.startswith(\"v\") else \"\"\n781:         return f\"{prefix}{new_v}\"\n782:     \n783:     if version_str.startswith(\"v\") and \".\" in version_str:\n784:         return f\"{version_str}.1\"\n785:     \n786:     return f\"{version_str}-1\"\n787: ```\n788: \n789: ### Docker Build Streaming\n790: \n791: ```python\n792: def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, \n793:                 image_name: str, tag: str, build_args: Optional[Dict]) -> Dict:\n794:     \"\"\"\n795:     Stream build logs for verbose output:\n796:     \"\"\"\n797:     import docker\n798:     import time\n799:     \n800:     client = docker.from_env()\n801:     full_tag = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n802:     start_time = time.time()\n803:     \n804:     build_kwargs = {\n805:         \"path\": str(context_path),\n806:         \"dockerfile\": str(dockerfile_path),\n807:         \"tag\": full_tag,\n808:         \"buildargs\": build_args,\n809:         \"decode\": True,\n810:     }\n811:     \n812:     for line in client.api.build(**build_kwargs):\n813:         if self.verbose and \"stream\" in line:\n814:             print(line[\"stream\"].strip())\n815:         if \"error\" in line:\n816:             raise docker.errors.BuildError(line[\"error\"], build_log)\n817:     \n818:     build_time = time.time() - start_time\n819:     \n820:     image = client.images.get(full_tag)\n821:     return {\n822:         \"image_name\": image_name,\n823:         \"image_id\": image.id,\n824:         \"image_size\": self._format_size(image.attrs[\"Size\"]),\n825:         \"build_time\": round(build_time, 2),\n826:         \"tag\": tag,\n827:     }\n828: ```\n829: \n830: ### Proxy Build Arg\n831: \n832: ```python\n833: def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, \n834:                  options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n835:     \"\"\"\n836:     Proxy handling:\n837:     \"\"\"\n838:     build_args = None\n839:     if options.get(\"proxy\"):\n840:         build_args = {\"PROXY\": options[\"proxy\"]}\n841:     \n842:     dockerfile_path = workspace_path / \"Dockerfile\"\n843:     \n844:     return self.docker_service.build_image(\n845:         dockerfile_path=dockerfile_path,\n846:         context_path=workspace_path,\n847:         image_name=metadata.agent_name,\n848:         tag=options.get(\"tag\", metadata.version or \"latest\"),\n849:         build_args=build_args,\n850:     )\n851: ```\n852: \n853: ### Metadata Update Pattern\n854: \n855: ```python\n856: def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata,\n857:                            build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None:\n858:     \"\"\"\n859:     Update metadata.image with build result:\n860:     \"\"\"\n861:     metadata.image = {\n862:         \"image_name\": build_result[\"image_name\"],\n863:         \"image_id\": build_result[\"image_id\"],\n864:         \"image_size\": build_result[\"image_size\"],\n865:         \"build_time\": build_result[\"build_time\"],\n866:         \"tag\": tag,\n867:     }\n868:     \n869:     self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n870: ```\n871: \n872: ### Rollback Pattern\n873: \n874: ```python\n875: def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n876:     \"\"\"\n877:     Full build with rollback:\n878:     \"\"\"\n879:     metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n880:     original_version = metadata.version\n881:     \n882:     self._validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n883:     \n884:     new_tag = self._increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)\n885:     \n886:     try:\n887:         if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n888:             result = self._build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n889:         else:\n890:             result = self._build_cloud(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n891:         \n892:         self._update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, result, new_tag)\n893:         return result\n894:         \n895:     except Exception as e:\n896:         # Rollback version\n897:         metadata.version = original_version\n898:         self.metadata_service.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)\n899:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Build failed: {e}. Version rolled back to {original_version}\")\n900: ```\n901: \n902: ---\n903: \n904: ## References\n905: \n906: - cli-toolkit/design.md — Overall CLI toolkit architecture\n907: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (Requirement: `build` command)\n908: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n909: - Typer Documentation: https://typer.tiangolo.com/\n910: - Rich Library: https://rich.readthedocs.io/\n911: - semver Python: https://python-semver.readthedocs.io/\n912: - AR-020 — CLI pack command (prerequisite, generates Dockerfile)\n913: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (follows build, uses image info)\n\n(End of file - total 913 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-021 — CLI build 命令 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-021 — CLI build 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nBuild command for AgentCube CLI that constructs container images from packaged agent workspaces. Orchestrates the full build lifecycle: prerequisite validation, version increment, Docker SDK build execution, and metadata persistence.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/design.md","time":{"start":1775870262475,"end":1775870262501}}}}
